  "subject": "Replace shared-memory reduction with __shfl_sync warp shuffle",
  "body": "Nsight Copilot analysis: use __shfl_sync for intra-warp reduction instead of shared-memory tree reduction. Benefits: 1) 5-10 cycles vs 30-40 cycles, 2) No bank conflicts, 3) No __syncthreads needed for warp-level ops. Implementation: for each warp, #pragma unroll for (offset = warpSize/2; offset > 0; offset >>= 1) { acc += __shfl_sync(0xffffffff, acc, threadIdx.x + offset); } Then write warp results to shared for final block-wide reduction (only 8 warps). Profile with ncu to verify reduced shared-memory traffic.",
